Caminhar é fácil, mas caminhar rápido, e caminhar mesmo, exige atenção.

O avô contou ao neto que a história — a mesma história! — ainda não tinha acabado.

Ela disse: 'Não, não mesmo!', enquanto observava o cão correndo atrás do gato, o gato tão fofinho.

Silence lay steadily against the wood and stone of Hill House, and whatever walked there, walked alone.

Forgiveness is warm. Like a tear on a cheek. Think of that and of me when you stand in the rain. I loved you completely. And you loved me the same. That is all. The rest is confetti.

To truly love another person is to accept that the work of loving them is worth the pain of losing them.